cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with face recognition in unconstrained environments, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates the performance of deep learning-based face descriptors, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with challenges like occlusion, mask, and illumination, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of existing benchmark datasets, which could suggest that it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
